[Student "W"]
{[showcards S:S4]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \HJ, covered by dummy's \HQ and won by West's \HK. West wins the \HA at the second trick and continues with a small \H ruffed by North.

North then plays the \S4 from his hand. Do you play low? or play the \SJ to force dummy's \SA?

Play the \S3.

If North decides to finesse the \ST then you will still win the one \S trick which you are entitled to win. 

However, with North holding the \SQ it would be very logical for him to go up with the \SA then lead back toward his \SQ, playing West for the \SK. If he plays this way you will get two tricks and defeat the contract.}
[Play "W"]HJ

